Posted @withrepost • @rob__banks PLEASE don’t support cruel companies like UGG. 
UGG uses sheep SKIN…meaning animals are killed for every single pair of boots. Adult, and baby sheep are both killed to make boots. 
You may only see the sheep wool inside of the boot, but it’s attached by the sheeps skin. 

Sheep are artificially impregnated, and in many cases the baby is taken from the mother shortly after being born. The baby will either be killed for lamb meat, and the skin sold for boots like this….or he/she will go up to be abused and killed like their mother. 

The thing that makes me so mad about this, are the people who continue to support cruel companies even after being educated. 
People making immature comments that they’re still going to wear these boots, as if it’s funny. 
Not to mention the selfish celebrities who promote such cruelty to millions of fans. How irresponsible can a person be?!
Lacking empathy for animals isn’t funny. It’s actually scary. 

This compilation of photos and videos here, is common practice in the sheep farming industry. So anyone who sells wool, shearling, sheepskin boots, etc is involved in the footage you see above in some way or another. 

The environmental impact and extreme animal cruelty that comes from the sheep farming business is absurd. Dangerous for the workers, toxic for the planet, and a death sentence for the animals. 
Please, I’m begging you…only support cruelty free companies. Not ones who use, abuse, and kill animals.
